th the Poblacion’s development is the development of its immediately adjacent barangays. The spatial design shall provide for flexibility in allowable uses to promote and support a dynamic interaction between the producing and consuming sectors of the municipality. The urban area of the municipality will not expand and will remain at 143.6391 hectares, representing 1.19% of the total municipal land area.&nbsp; The resulting functional land uses are discussed below and quantities are tabulated in Table No. 3, Existing and Proposed Land Uses, Urban and Figure No. 4, Comparative Proposed Urban Land Uses).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Functional Land Uses in the Urban Area</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li><strong><em>Residential Use / Residential Subdivision</em></strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is characterized by mixed dwelling types, dwelling accessories, and customary facilities of the area that shall promote its self-containment such as home occupations and the like.&nbsp; The residential area has been increased from 35.0900 hectares to 35.7000hectares.&nbsp; This represents 24.85% of the total urban land area. Expansion of the residential areas in Poblacionminimally accommodated. Existing subdivisions account for an area of 4.3596 hectares whichhelp accommodate residentialexpansion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li><strong><em>Commercial / Industrial Use</em></strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Commercial activities are expected to intensify in Burgos with the growth impulse to be brought about by the intensification of activities in Poblacion or urban center. The commercial activities will be concentrated