 sectors in support of the PNP, BFP, and CVOs in the civic responsibility of community protection during periods of crisis &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Poblacion &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>First three years of planning period &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period</td><td>LGU, PNP &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, PNP &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, PNP, DILG &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, PNP, DILG &nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>6. Sports and Recreation</td><td>To upgrade all&nbsp; existing sports and recreational facilities by the end of the planning period &nbsp; To repackage open spaces and sports and recreation areas for tourism outdoor activities based on a tourism plan &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned Agencies &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies</td></tr><tr><td>B. ECONOMIC</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>1. Agriculture</td><td>To increase the average yield of palay of in irrigated areas and rain-fed areas by 50% during the whole planning period &nbsp; To prepare a comprehensive agricultural master plan identifying the best suitable and profitable crops in all barangays, particularly in the barangays of Concordia, Sapa Grande and SapaPequena by the first year of the planning period &nbsp; To prepare a plan for livestock production and marketing in the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; &nbsp; To prepare a special plan for the management of pasturelands and open spaces, in connection with tourism plans, within the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; &nbsp; To declare unclassified forests as protected forests and prepare a forest management plan for the municipality within the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; To expand the coverage of the lives