and timely capital assistance for income generation</li><li>To provide livelihood opportunities</li><li>To reduce malnutrition cases in preschool children</li><li>To promote gender awareness and understanding of women issues and concerns</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.STRATEGIES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1. Agriculture</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.1. Crops</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Declare agricultural lands as SAFDZ areas</li><li>Planning for pasturelands and open spaces</li><li>Promotion of rice production technology using hybrid variety<strong></strong></li><li>Rehabilitation and maintenance of irrigation systems in irrigated barangays and expansion of irrigable areas<strong></strong></li><li>Construction of post-harvest facilities<strong></strong></li></ul><ul><li>Promotion of intensified and diversified rice based integrated farming system incorporating high value crops<strong></strong></li><li>Promotion of commercially viable and exportable crops <strong></strong></li><li>Implementation of production cost reduction technologies on rice, corn, and organic farming technology<strong></strong></li><li>Strengthening of cooperatives and farmers’ groups and organizations<strong></strong></li><li>Assisting of&nbsp; cooperatives who avail of loans from lending institutions <strong></strong></li><li>Establishment of techno-demo for identified crops adopting new technology<strong></strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.2. Livestock</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Promotion and dissemination of improved technology on livestock and poultry production</li><li>Encouraging of backyard poultry production</li><li>Upgrading of chicken breeds</li><li>Promotion on animal health care and disease management</li><li>Improvement of municipal slaughterhouse</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.3. Rural Infrastructure</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Provision of year-round irrigation to increase crop production</li><li>Provision of infrastructure support services (irrigation, farm-to-market roads, bridges, post-harvest facilities)<strong></strong></li><li>Promotion of information technology for wider access to agriculture and aquaculture information.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.4. Institutional Capability Building</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Strengthening of cooperatives, farmers’ organizations</li><li>Establish marketing with line agencies and credit linkages for loan<strong></strong></li><li>Provision of livelihood assistance to farmer beneficiaries through viable cooperative organizations</li><li>Provision of training on leadership, management, agribusiness, market and financial networking with private institutions</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.5. Marketing System and Agri-business Development</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Promotion of competitive agricultural products for domestic and international market demands</li><li>Conduct annual assessment and evaluation of agricultural performance to determine marketing demand of crops<strong></strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.1.6. Human Resource Development</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Upgrading of skills through training and other educational activities to enhance extension delivery activities</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.2. Commerce and Industry</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Develop the Poblacion and adjacent barangays as a growth area by being a central business district and introducing supply and support facilities in the aforementioned areas</li><li>Pave with concrete and/or asphalt roads in the potential commercial centers</li><li>Provide funds for the improvement of the existing public market and its annexes</li><li>Improve market and business tax collection and revenue raising schemes for reinvestment into commercial sector infrastructure</li><li>Provide entrepreneurial and business management training for local residents and set up trade fairs</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.3. Infrastructure and Tourism</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Exercise vigilance and care in all major intersections and trunk lines in order to keep roads and passageways safe for both life and property.</li><li>Acquisition of water rights, and seeking professional consultations with the Local Water Utilities Authority on water resources management.</li><li>Upgrade and modernize the power supply distribution facilities in the municipality.</li><li>Monitor and /or maintain the performance of existing facilities.</li><li>Unite tourism plans agriculture and commercial plans</li><li>Revitalize beach tourism in coastal barangay</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.4. Social Services</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Elementary and secondary school facilities should be made accessible to all</li><li>Teacher training registration fees should be allocated from the Educational Support Fund (ESF)</li><li>Items for security guards especially for the National High Schools should be allocated from the ESF</li><li>The distribution of the ESF to public schools should be on a per capita basis and all school heads should be given the opportunity to identify their priority targets</li><li>Municipal government-owned lots used as school sites should be transferred to the Department of Education</li><li>Coordinate with the Technical Education and Skills Development Authority (TESDA) and the Commission on Higher Education (CHED) for the immediate establishment of such institutions</li><li>Promotion of Primary Health Care</li><li>Greater Emphasis on Promotive and Preventive Health Care</li><li>Strict Implementation of Existing Ordinances on Solid Waste Management</li><li>Increased Budgetary Allocation for the Purchase of Medicine and Medical Supplies</li><li>Sourcing of funding support for day care centers</li><li>Allocation of funds for livelihood and income generating projects</li><li>Intensification of the nutrition program thru massive supplemental feeding to malnourished children</li><li>Coordination with TESDA TLRC for skills development training for youth and&nbsp; mothers</li><li>Identification and listing of potential clients and community leaders</li><li>Activation and strengthening of existing organizations for disaster management and preparedness</li><li>Strengthening of the participation of NGOs to promote and implement programs through linkages and proper coordination</li><li>Training and mobilization of community volunteers and organization of the welfare structure</li><li>Putting up of Day Care Centers</li><li>Organization of an Out of School Youth (OSY) Groups</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'GOALS, OBJECTIVES, STRATEGIES', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '106-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-09-14 14:28:53', '2020-09-14 14:28:53', '', 106, 'https://192.168.1.5/git/burgos-website/?p=311', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
